### Login (response token is captured into {{token}} below)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "fleet@transitops.dev",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Token captured from the login response above
@token = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### Current user (session restore endpoint for the frontend)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJjbXJoanM0a3AwMDAzb3h2eTZyNjB0YTVnIiwiZW1haWwiOiJmbGVldEB0cmFuc2l0b3BzLmRldiIsIm5hbWUiOiJGYXRpbWEgS2hhbiIsInJvbGUiOiJGTEVFVF9NQU5BR0VSIiwiaWF0IjoxNzgzODQ2MTE3LCJleHAiOjE3ODM4NzQ5MTd9.LBpjNvzWVxBapZgoTMohxuk52Opwhh7eEJ7kO0IGKAg

### Login with wrong password → expect 401, generic message
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "fleet@transitops.dev",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}

### /me without a token → expect 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

### Register with invalid role → expect 400 with field details
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Bad Role",
  "email": "bad@transitops.dev",
  "password": "password123",
  "role": "ADMIN"
}